  "time_ut": 1657547265,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dad\u0ddd\u0dbb\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0da2\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2 20 \u0daf\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Election of the President on July 20",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "After summoning the Parliament on Friday 15th July and declaring that there is a vacancy in the office of the President in accordance with the provisions of the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981, nominations will be called on Tuesday the 19th and a vote will be held on Wednesday the 20th according to the provisions of the existing laws and the new President will be elected. Mr. Mahanda Yapa Abeywardena, a speaker, says that it was decided at the party leader's meeting held today that it should be done.",
        "\"A meeting of party leaders was held today at 2:00 pm at the Parliament complex under my chairmanship. The main purpose of that meeting was that the current president has announced to me that he will resign from office on July 13, so the next steps to be taken very soon and basically all Aiming to discuss the formation of a party government.",
        "At this time, the party leaders emphasized that this work should be done in a very short time in accordance with Article 40 of the Constitution and the Election of the President (Special Provisions) Act No. 2 of 1981.",
        "Accordingly, Parliament was convened on Friday 15th July and after declaring that there is a vacancy in the office of the President in accordance with the provisions of the relevant Act, it was decided that nominations should be called on Tuesday 19th and a vote held on Wednesday 20th according to the provisions of the law to elect the immediate past President.",
        "The party leaders expressed their views here that arrangements should be made for the formation of an all-party government under the new president and for the future constitutional work to be carried out and for the continuation of the existing essential services in the country.",
        "Mr. Prasanna Ranatunga, the chief organizer of the ruling party, said that the cabinet including the Prime Minister is ready to leave tomorrow or if an all-party government is to be formed.",
        "I also stated that I expect the support of all party leaders to make these activities successful,\" the speaker said in a statement about the party leaders' meeting held today."
      ],
